464 
465 AND THEY LAUGHED
466 
467 
468 By the mountain peak, called “Going-To-The-Sun,”
469 A dizzy mountain, where paths twist round and round
470 And nothing in sober order can be found--
471 I asked the poppies: “What fairies do you see?”
472 And they shook their long stems, and they laughed at me.
473 
