486 
487 THE FAIRY CIRCUS
488 
489 
490 A fairy ran a circus
491 With a pigeon puffed and proud,
492 A humble bullfrog
493 And a rather solid cloud.
494 
495 She wore her underwear,
496 The rest wore what they had,
497 The frog wore a blue coat
498 Just like his dad.
499 
500 The pigeon wore his feathers
501 And spread himself--O My!
502 The cloud wore sunshine
503 He gathered in the sky.
504 
505 [Illustration]
506 
507 
508 
509 
510 THE BATTLE-AX OF THE SUN
511 
512 
513 On the mountain peak I reached the drift
514 And I took it for a Christmas gift,
515 And I made ten soldiers out of snow.
516 
517 But the battle-ax of my fairy foe
518 Cut to the ground my men of snow.
519 
520 And who was he, my fairy foe,
521 Who brought my snowy army low?
522 
523 The mountain sun was my fairy foe.
524 
525 [Illustration: THE BATTLE-AX OF THE SUN]
